00:00:01.380 --> 00:00:05.720
Prof: Today's case,
SELCO SEWA,

00:00:05.720 --> 00:00:19.290
is a wonderful transition to
Collier's Bottom Billion

00:00:19.290 --> 00:00:22.779
and a--
I want to start with some

00:00:22.779 --> 00:00:25.390
frameworks and I'm going to do
these briefly.

00:00:25.390 --> 00:00:27.930
I'll post them this evening so
you can look back at them.

00:00:27.930 --> 00:00:32.459
I want to introduce--these are
very standard MBA-ish,

00:00:32.459 --> 00:00:36.640
shorthand frameworks for
thinking about cases.

00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:40.496
You heard, I think most of
this, but I should rub it in a

00:00:40.496 --> 00:00:40.910
bit.
 

00:00:40.910 --> 00:00:46.550
One is called SWOT,
and this one has really no

00:00:46.550 --> 00:00:53.301
analytical content to it,
it's just a way of organizing

00:00:53.301 --> 00:00:58.554
your thoughts on a topic,
strengths, weaknesses,

00:00:58.554 --> 00:01:01.048
opportunities,
threat.

00:01:01.048 --> 00:01:05.096
In the temporal dimension
typically the strengths and

00:01:05.096 --> 00:01:09.611
weaknesses are things which are
immediately present in your

00:01:09.611 --> 00:01:13.468
situation,
and the opportunities and

00:01:13.468 --> 00:01:19.384
threats are things you might
have happen to you or might

00:01:19.384 --> 00:01:21.319
cause to occur.
 

00:01:21.319 --> 00:01:27.668
A lot of back of the envelope
thinking about business cases is

00:01:27.668 --> 00:01:30.790
organized in this shorthand.
 

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:35.989
You might make yourself a grid
like,

00:01:35.989 --> 00:01:38.209
this and let the column heading
be SWOT,

00:01:38.209 --> 00:01:45.060
and then let the row headings
be whatever you choose,

00:01:45.060 --> 00:01:49.720
but one candidate is the Porter
forces,

00:01:49.720 --> 00:01:52.720
which we've seen before.
 

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:56.596
How fierce is the direct
competition in your business

00:01:56.596 --> 00:02:00.995
from other people doing more or
less exactly what you do and

00:02:00.995 --> 00:02:03.680
trying to do it better than you?
 

00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:07.516
What's the threat that others
not now doing it will enter the

00:02:07.516 --> 00:02:09.818
business and increase
competition?

00:02:09.818 --> 00:02:15.834
How likely is it that people
will find substitutes for your

00:02:15.834 --> 00:02:20.085
whole industry,
that your industry will be

00:02:20.085 --> 00:02:24.128
undermined by an adjacent
industry?

00:02:24.128 --> 00:02:32.770
I could tell--I was able to
determine which letter it was.

00:02:32.770 --> 00:02:36.068
Can you hold that up and tell
us what it's about?

