added service out there.

00:08:20.819 --> 00:08:25.415
It turns out that taking
responsibility for durable goods

00:08:25.415 --> 00:08:29.206
that you sell,
there's not much long term

00:08:29.206 --> 00:08:33.629
responsibility for toothbrushes
or toothpicks,

00:08:33.629 --> 00:08:38.595
but there is a lot of service
responsibility for any form of

00:08:38.595 --> 00:08:41.092
machinery,
especially when people are

00:08:41.092 --> 00:08:43.899
going to organize their lives
around the machinery.

00:08:43.899 --> 00:08:52.162
The classic insight on--classic
example on this is on McCormick

00:08:52.162 --> 00:08:56.158
farm machinery in the 1800s.
 

00:08:56.158 --> 00:08:59.929
The brilliant thing they did,
which none of their competitors

00:08:59.929 --> 00:09:02.870
did,
was to manufacture only during

00:09:02.870 --> 00:09:07.706
the winter season and use the
same people that were running

00:09:07.706 --> 00:09:12.792
the manufacturing plant to be
servicing agents for the farmers

00:09:12.792 --> 00:09:17.461
during the growing season so
that the advantage of buying

00:09:17.461 --> 00:09:21.879
their stuff had everything to do
with service.

